{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EaXxbuhPZGVvWX7YhbjerA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to create a comprehensive migration plan. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n**Current State:**\n- RabbitMQ version: 3.12.14 (out of support as per the status output)\n- Erlang/OTP: 25 (erts-13.2.2.15)\n- 3-node cluster, all disk nodes, all running\n\n**Vhosts:**\n- `/` (default)\n- `/app`\n- `/ops`\n\n**Users:**\n- `admin` - administrator tag\n- `app-user` - management tag\n- `ops-user` - management tag\n\n**Permissions:**\n- `/` vhost: admin has full access\n- `/app` vhost: admin and app-user both have full access\n- `/ops` vhost: admin and ops-user both have full access\n\n**Queues:**\n- `/app` vhost: `app-queue` (classic, durable, 575 messages, no consumers)\n- `/ops` vhost: `ops-queue` (classic, durable, empty, no consumers)\n\n**Policies:**\n- `/app` vhost has an `ha-all` policy configured for high availability across all queues with automatic synchronization\n\nThe cluster is set up with Kubernetes peer discovery through a headless service, configured to handle network partitions by pausing the minority partition. Feature flags are all enabled including quorum and stream queue support. The current version 3.12.14 is out of support, so I need to plan an upgrade path through several intermediate versions to reach a supported release.\n\nThe main challenge is that classic mirrored queues using the `ha-all` policy were deprecated in 3.13 and completely removed in 4.0, so those need to be converted to quorum queues before upgrading past 3.13. I also need to address the `queue_master_locator` setting which is deprecated in newer versions. There's also the `app-queue` sitting with 575 unprocessed messages and no consumers, which represents a risk I should handle during the migration.\n\nMy migration strategy should prioritize converting the classic mirrored queues to quorum queues first, then proceed with the version upgrades through the supported path.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1014,"cache_read_input_tokens":36065,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1014},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a73a9b8-ff7b-4701-9712-25cb1b94fa82","uuid":"57be9c2d-03d1-4fe0-b832-8136670e3a25","request_id":"req_011CcMUjPA6xYNhmAVd8FHYR"}
