{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EaXxbuhPZGVvWX7YhbjerA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011iiooNmxBSL8BRHyuCTCrk","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23  \n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e5b25a86-cluster-a`  \n**Author:** Operations Team (pre-change-window audit)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as found)\n\n### 1.1 Software Versions\n\n| Component | Version |\n|-----------|---------|\n| RabbitMQ  | **3.12.14** — out of support (EOL) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25 (erts-13.2.2.15) |\n\nAll three nodes are running identical versions.\n\n### 1.2 Cluster Topology\n\n- **Nodes:** 3 disk nodes (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2)\n- **Cluster name:** `rabbit@rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local`\n- **Peer discovery:** Kubernetes headless service (`rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s`)\n- **Partition handling:** `pause_minority`\n- **No alarms, no network partitions, no nodes under maintenance**\n\n### 1.3 Enabled Plugins\n\n`rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`\n\n### 1.4 Virtual Hosts\n\n| vhost | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `/`   | Default (no application queues) |\n| `/app` | Application workload |\n| `/ops` | Operations/monitoring workload |\n\n### 1.5 Users and Permissions\n\n| User | Tags | `/` | `/app` | `/ops` |\n|------|------|-----|--------|--------|\n| `admin` | administrator | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |\n| `app-user` | management | — | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | — |\n| `ops-user` | management | — | — | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |\n\n### 1.6 Queues\n\n| vhost | Queue | Type | Durable | Messages | Consumers |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|----------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | yes | 575 | 0 |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | yes | 0 | 0 |\n\n`app-queue` has **575 unprocessed messages and no active consumers** — a backlog risk.\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\n| vhost | Name | Pattern | Applies-to | Definition | Priority |\n|-------|------|---------|------------|------------|----------|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `.*` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies on `/ops` or `/`.\n\n### 1.8 Exchanges and Bindings (/app)\n\nDefault AMQP exchanges only (amq.direct, amq.topic, amq.fanout, amq.headers, amq.match).  \n`app-queue` is bound to the default exchange with routing key `app-queue`.\n\n### 1.9 Feature Flags (all enabled)\n\n`classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `stream_single_active_consumer`,\n`maintenance_mode_status`, `feature_flags_v2`, `user_limits`, `virtual_host_metadata`, and others — full set enabled.\n\n### 1.10 Key Config Settings\n\n```\ncluster_partition_handling    = pause_minority\nqueue_master_locator          = min-masters\nloopback_users.guest          = false\nlisteners.tcp.default         = 5672\nmanagement.tcp.port           = 15672\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Identified\n\n### P0 — Critical (block upgrade)\n\n**P0-1: Classic mirrored queues on a deprecated policy**  \nThe `ha-all` policy on `/app` sets `ha-mode: all` with classic mirroring. Classic mirrored queues were deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.13 and **fully removed in 4.0**. Upgrading to 4.x without first converting `app-queue` and `ops-queue` to quorum queues will cause those queues to be silently converted or fail.  \n*Action required: migrate both queues to quorum queues before upgrading past 3.13.*\n\n**P0-2: RabbitMQ 3.12.x is end-of-life**  \n3.12 receives no security patches. Target: 3.13.x → 4.0.x → 4.1.x (sequential; no version skipping is supported).\n\n**P0-3: `app-queue` has 575 unread messages and zero consumers**  \nThe consumer (`app-client`) may be disconnected or crashed. If the queue is deleted or recreated during migration, these messages will be lost. Drain or snapshot the queue before any destructive operation.\n\n### P1 — Should fix before next release\n\n**P1-1: `queue_master_locator = min-masters` is deprecated**  \nThis setting is ignored on quorum/stream queues and has been removed from the documentation path in 4.x. Remove it from `rabbitmq.conf` when updating for quorum queues.\n\n**P1-2: `app-user` and `ops-user` have `.*`/`.*`/`.*` (full) permissions on their respective vhosts**  \nPrinciple of least privilege: application users should be limited to the specific queues and exchanges they need. Consider scoping configure/write/read patterns more tightly (e.g., `^app-queue$` for `app-user`).\n\n**P1-3: No policies on `/ops` vhost**  \n`ops-queue` has no high-availability or durability policy. If `ops-queue` requires the same resilience guarantee as `app-queue`, it needs a quorum-queue policy applied.\n\n### P2 — Observe / low-priority\n\n**P2-1: Erlang/OTP 25 should be updated alongside RabbitMQ**  \nRabbitMQ 4.x requires Erlang 26+. The Erlang version must be upgraded in the same image bump.\n\n**P2-2: No `x-dead-letter-exchange` on `app-queue`**  \nWith 575 stale messages and no DLX, rejected/expired messages will be dropped. Consider adding a DLX for operational visibility.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Path\n\nThe mandatory version sequence for zero-skip rolling upgrades:\n\n```\n3.12.14 (current)\n  → 3.13.x   [Erlang 26+]   — classic mirroring deprecated but still functional\n  → 4.0.x    [Erlang 26+]   — classic mirroring REMOVED; quorum queues required\n  → 4.1.x    [Erlang 26+]   — current stable\n```\n\nEach hop is a rolling StatefulSet upgrade: one pod at a time, wait for `cluster_status` to show the node rejoined before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Change Plan — Step-by-Step\n\n> **These steps are NOT applied yet.** This plan requires review and approval before execution. Apply only during the scheduled change window with a designated rollback engineer on call.\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (Day of window, before any changes)\n\n0. Confirm no alarms: `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` — all 3 nodes Running, 0 alarms.\n1. Drain or snapshot `app-queue` (575 messages). If consumers can be restarted, do so and wait for `messages = 0`. Otherwise, use `rabbitmqadmin export` to back up definitions and messages to a durable store.\n2. Export definitions backup:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json\n   ```\n3. Confirm `app-client` and `app-producer` pods are healthy and the queue is actively being drained.\n\n### Phase 1 — Migrate queues to Quorum (on 3.12.14)\n\nQuorum queues are already supported on 3.12 and all feature flags are enabled, so this migration can happen before the version upgrade.\n\n1. **Remove the classic `ha-all` policy on `/app`:**\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all\n   ```\n\n2. **Create a quorum-queue policy on `/app`:**\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app quorum-default \".*\" \\\n     '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' \\\n     --apply-to queues --priority 0\n   ```\n   Note: This policy only affects newly declared queues. Existing classic queues must be migrated by re-declaration.\n\n3. **Migrate `app-queue` from classic to quorum:**\n   - Stop producers (scale `app-producer` to 0 replicas temporarily).\n   - Wait for `messages = 0` in `app-queue` (or shovel messages out).\n   - Delete the existing classic queue: `rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue`\n   - Re-declare with quorum type: `rabbitmqctl declare_queue -p /app --type quorum --durable app-queue`\n   - Resume producers.\n\n4. **Migrate `ops-queue` from classic to quorum** (same procedure on `/ops` vhost).\n   - Apply a quorum policy on `/ops`:\n     ```bash\n     rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /ops quorum-default \".*\" \\\n       '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' --apply-to queues --priority 0\n     ```\n   - Delete and re-declare `ops-queue` as quorum type.\n\n5. **Verify quorum queue leaders and members:**\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state leader members\n   rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state leader members\n   ```\n   Each quorum queue should show a leader on one node and members on all three.\n\n### Phase 2 — Update `rabbitmq.conf`\n\nRemove the deprecated `queue_master_locator = min-masters` line from the ConfigMap / Secret backing `rabbitmq.conf`. Apply via a rolling restart after Phase 1 is verified.\n\n### Phase 3 — Version Upgrade: 3.12.14 → 3.13.x\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image tag to the target 3.13.x image (Erlang 26 base).\n2. Perform a rolling upgrade: patch one pod at a time.\n   ```bash\n   # For each pod (rabbitmq-2, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-0 — reverse order):\n   kubectl rollout restart statefulset/rabbitmq   # or use partition-based rolling\n   ```\n   Wait between each pod: confirm the node rejoins with `rabbitmqctl cluster_status`.\n3. After all pods are on 3.13.x, enable any new 3.13 feature flags:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n\n### Phase 4 — Version Upgrade: 3.13.x → 4.0.x / 4.1.x\n\n1. Repeat the rolling upgrade procedure with the 4.0.x (or 4.1.x) image.\n2. Classic mirrored queues must already be gone (Phase 1). Verify no classic mirroring policies remain.\n3. Enable remaining 4.x feature flags post-upgrade.\n\n### Phase 5 — Tighten Permissions (P1-2)\n\nAfter upgrade is stable, scope `app-user` and `ops-user` permissions to least privilege:\n\n```bash\n# app-user: can only write to and read from app-queue; cannot configure\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"\" \"^app-queue$\" \"^app-queue$\"\n\n# ops-user: can only write to and read from ops-queue; cannot configure\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \"\" \"^ops-queue$\" \"^ops-queue$\"\n```\n\nValidate application connectivity before removing broader permissions.\n\n### Phase 6 — Add DLX to `app-queue` (P2-2, optional)\n\nDeclare a dead-letter exchange on `/app` and configure `app-queue` with `x-dead-letter-exchange`. Requires requeue/redeclare of the queue (already done in Phase 1 as a quorum queue).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\n| Phase | Rollback Action |\n|-------|----------------|\n| Phase 1 (policy change) | Re-apply `ha-all` policy; re-declare classic queues from definitions backup |\n| Phase 2 (config) | Restore previous rabbitmq.conf from ConfigMap backup; rolling restart |\n| Phase 3 (3.13 upgrade) | Roll back StatefulSet image to 3.12.14; rolling restart. Note: feature flags enabled in 3.13 may not be reversible |\n| Phase 4 (4.x upgrade) | Roll back to 3.13.x image. Classic queue removal in 4.x is irreversible — do not attempt to roll back to classic queues from 4.x |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Acceptance Criteria\n\nAfter the change window, verify:\n\n- [ ] All 3 nodes running the target version (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`)\n- [ ] No alarms (`rabbitmqctl list_alarms`)\n- [ ] `app-queue` and `ops-queue` are type `quorum` with leaders and members on all 3 nodes\n- [ ] No `ha-mode` policies remain\n- [ ] `app-client` and `app-producer` consuming and publishing without errors\n- [ ] Prometheus metrics endpoint reachable at `:15692/metrics`\n- [ ] `ops-client` reachable\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1014,"cache_read_input_tokens":36065,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1014},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a73a9b8-ff7b-4701-9712-25cb1b94fa82","uuid":"fac1ab56-cf9c-4941-b266-625c4c59a27b","request_id":"req_011CcMUjPA6xYNhmAVd8FHYR"}
