{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FM3a5yDraxdEXXqzc8eMqB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UAtiahP6MsTUNzMhpZkXuK","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e5b25a86-cluster-a`\n**Author:** Operations Team (pre-change-window audit)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as found)\n\n### 1.1 Software Versions\n\n| Component | Version |\n|-----------|---------|\n| RabbitMQ  | **3.12.14** — out of support (EOL) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25 (erts-13.2.2.15) |\n\nAll three nodes are running identical versions.\n\n### 1.2 Cluster Topology\n\n- **Nodes:** 3 disk nodes (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2)\n- **Cluster name:** `rabbit@rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local`\n- **Peer discovery:** Kubernetes headless service (`rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s`)\n- **Partition handling:** `pause_minority`\n- **No alarms, no network partitions, no nodes under maintenance**\n\n### 1.3 Enabled Plugins\n\n`rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`,\n`rabbitmq_management_agent`\n\n### 1.4 Virtual Hosts\n\n| vhost  | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `/`    | Default (no application queues) |\n| `/app` | Application workload |\n| `/ops` | Operations/monitoring workload |\n\n### 1.5 Users and Permissions\n\n| User       | Tags          | `/`          | `/app`       | `/ops`       |\n|------------|---------------|--------------|--------------|--------------|\n| `admin`    | administrator | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |\n| `app-user` | management    | —            | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | —            |\n| `ops-user` | management    | —            | —            | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |\n\n### 1.6 Queues\n\n| vhost  | Queue       | Type    | Durable | Messages | Consumers |\n|--------|-------------|---------|---------|----------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | yes     | 575      | 0         |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | yes     | 0        | 0         |\n\n`app-queue` has **575 unprocessed messages and no active consumers** — a backlog risk.\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\n| vhost  | Name     | Pattern | Applies-to | Definition | Priority |\n|--------|----------|---------|------------|------------|----------|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `.*`    | queues     | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies on `/ops` or `/`.\n\n### 1.8 Exchanges and Bindings (/app)\n\nDefault AMQP exchanges only (amq.direct, amq.topic, amq.fanout, amq.headers, amq.match).\n`app-queue` is bound to the default exchange with routing key `app-queue`.\n\n### 1.9 Feature Flags (all enabled)\n\n`classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`,\n`stream_single_active_consumer`, `maintenance_mode_status`, `feature_flags_v2`,\n`user_limits`, `virtual_host_metadata`, and others — full set enabled.\n\n### 1.10 Key Config Settings\n\n```\ncluster_partition_handling = pause_minority\nqueue_master_locator       = min-masters\nloopback_users.guest       = false\nlisteners.tcp.default      = 5672\nmanagement.tcp.port        = 15672\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Identified\n\n### P0 — Critical (must resolve before upgrade)\n\n**P0-1: Classic mirrored queues — deprecated and removed in 4.0**\nThe `ha-all` policy on `/app` uses `ha-mode: all` (classic mirroring). Classic\nmirrored queues were deprecated in 3.13 and **fully removed in 4.0**. Both\n`app-queue` (classic) and `ops-queue` (classic, no policy) must be converted to\nquorum queues before upgrading to 4.x.\n\n**P0-2: RabbitMQ 3.12.x is end-of-life**\n3.12 no longer receives security patches. Upgrade is required.\n\n**P0-3: 575 unread messages in `app-queue` with zero consumers**\nThe `app-client` consumer appears disconnected. These messages will be lost if the\nqueue is deleted during migration. Must drain or snapshot before any destructive\nqueue operation.\n\n### P1 — Should fix before next release\n\n**P1-1: `queue_master_locator = min-masters` is deprecated**\nThis setting is ignored by quorum/stream queues and has been removed in 4.x.\nRemove from `rabbitmq.conf` when updating config for the upgrade.\n\n**P1-2: `app-user` and `ops-user` have full permissions (`.*`)**\nPrinciple of least privilege: application users should be scoped to the queues and\nexchanges they actually use. Broadening to `.*` on configure allows these users to\ndeclare/delete any resource in their vhost.\n\n**P1-3: No HA/durability policy on `/ops` vhost**\n`ops-queue` is a classic durable queue but has no resilience policy. If it requires\nthe same availability guarantee as `app-queue`, it needs a quorum-queue policy.\n\n### P2 — Observe / low-priority\n\n**P2-1: Erlang/OTP 25 must be updated alongside RabbitMQ**\nRabbitMQ 4.x requires Erlang 26+. The Erlang upgrade must be bundled into the same\nimage change.\n\n**P2-2: No dead-letter exchange (DLX) on `app-queue`**\nWith 575 stale messages and no DLX, rejected or TTL-expired messages are silently\ndropped. Consider adding a DLX for operational visibility.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Required Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ does not support skipping major versions. The mandatory sequence:\n\n```\n3.12.14 (current, EOL)\n  -> 3.13.x   [Erlang 26+]   classic mirroring deprecated but still functional\n  -> 4.0.x    [Erlang 26+]   classic mirroring REMOVED; quorum queues required by here\n  -> 4.1.x    [Erlang 26+]   current stable\n```\n\nEach hop is a rolling StatefulSet upgrade: one pod at a time, verify the node\nrejoins the cluster before proceeding to the next pod.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Change Plan — Step-by-Step\n\n> **IMPORTANT: None of these steps have been applied. This plan requires sign-off\n> before execution. Apply only during the scheduled change window with a rollback\n> engineer available.**\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (day of change window, before any changes)\n\n1. Confirm cluster health:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n   ```\n   All 3 nodes must be Running. Zero alarms. No network partitions.\n\n2. Snapshot `app-queue` messages. If `app-client` can be restarted, do so and\n   wait for `messages = 0`. Otherwise export a definitions + message backup:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json\n   # Use rabbitmqadmin or the HTTP API to shovel/export messages if needed.\n   ```\n\n3. Export definitions backup (also covers vhosts, users, permissions, policies):\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json\n   ```\n\n4. Confirm `app-producer` and `app-client` pod health in Kubernetes.\n\n### Phase 1 — Migrate queues to Quorum (on 3.12.14, before any version bump)\n\nQuorum queues are already supported on 3.12 and all feature flags are enabled.\n\n**Step 1a — Remove the classic ha-all policy on /app:**\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all\n```\n\n**Step 1b — Add a quorum-queue policy on /app:**\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app quorum-default \".*\" \\\n  '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' \\\n  --apply-to queues --priority 0\n```\nThis policy governs newly declared queues. Existing classic queues must be\nre-declared.\n\n**Step 1c — Migrate app-queue (classic -> quorum):**\n- Pause producers: scale `app-producer` Deployment to 0.\n- Drain `app-queue` to 0 messages (consumers, or shovel to a staging queue).\n- Delete the classic queue:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n  ```\n- Re-declare as quorum:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqadmin -V /app declare queue name=app-queue durable=true \\\n    arguments='{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}'\n  ```\n- Resume producers: scale `app-producer` back to 1.\n\n**Step 1d — Migrate ops-queue (classic -> quorum):**\n- Apply a quorum policy on /ops:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /ops quorum-default \".*\" \\\n    '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' --apply-to queues --priority 0\n  ```\n- Delete and re-declare `ops-queue`:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /ops ops-queue\n  rabbitmqadmin -V /ops declare queue name=ops-queue durable=true \\\n    arguments='{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}'\n  ```\n\n**Step 1e — Verify quorum queues:**\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state leader members\nrabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state leader members\n```\nEach queue must show `type=quorum`, a `leader` on one node, and `members` listing\nall three nodes.\n\n### Phase 2 — Update rabbitmq.conf\n\nRemove `queue_master_locator = min-masters` from the ConfigMap or Secret backing\n`rabbitmq.conf`. Apply via a rolling restart of the StatefulSet after Phase 1 is\nverified stable.\n\n### Phase 3 — Version Upgrade: 3.12.14 -> 3.13.x\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image tag to the target 3.13.x image (with Erlang 26 base).\n2. Rolling upgrade — one pod at a time in reverse ordinal order (rabbitmq-2 first):\n   ```bash\n   # Use a partition-based rolling update or manual pod-by-pod:\n   kubectl rollout restart statefulset/rabbitmq -n <ns>\n   ```\n   After each pod restarts, wait until it rejoins:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status | grep -A5 \"Running Nodes\"\n   ```\n3. After all pods are on 3.13.x, enable any new feature flags:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n4. Verify: all alarms clear, quorum queues healthy, consumers reconnected.\n\n### Phase 4 — Version Upgrade: 3.13.x -> 4.0.x or 4.1.x\n\nRepeat the rolling upgrade procedure with the 4.0.x or 4.1.x image. At this point\nclassic mirrored queues must already be gone (Phase 1). Verify no `ha-mode` policies\nremain before starting:\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl list_policies --all-vhosts\n# Must show no ha-mode definitions\n```\n\nEnable remaining 4.x feature flags post-upgrade:\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n```\n\n### Phase 5 — Tighten Permissions (P1-2, post-upgrade)\n\nScope `app-user` and `ops-user` to least privilege after the upgrade is confirmed stable:\n\n```bash\n# app-user: write and read only to app-queue; no configure rights\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"\" \"^app-queue$\" \"^app-queue$\"\n\n# ops-user: write and read only to ops-queue; no configure rights\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \"\" \"^ops-queue$\" \"^ops-queue$\"\n```\n\nTest application connectivity before removing broader permissions.\n\n### Phase 6 — Add DLX to app-queue (P2-2, optional / future window)\n\nDeclare a dead-letter exchange on `/app` and attach it to `app-queue` via the\n`x-dead-letter-exchange` argument. This requires another queue re-declaration\n(safe since Phase 1 already converted it to quorum).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\n| Phase | Rollback Action |\n|-------|----------------|\n| Phase 1 (policy + queue type) | Re-apply `ha-all` policy; restore classic queues from definitions backup |\n| Phase 2 (config) | Restore previous `rabbitmq.conf` from ConfigMap backup; rolling restart |\n| Phase 3 (3.13 upgrade) | Roll back StatefulSet image to 3.12.14; rolling restart. Note: some 3.13 feature flags are not reversible |\n| Phase 4 (4.x upgrade) | Roll back to 3.13.x image. Classic queue removal in 4.x is irreversible — do not attempt to roll back to classic queues from 4.x |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Acceptance Criteria\n\nAfter the change window, verify ALL of the following before sign-off:\n\n- [ ] All 3 nodes running the target version (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`)\n- [ ] No alarms (`rabbitmqctl list_alarms`)\n- [ ] `app-queue` and `ops-queue` are type `quorum`, each with a leader and\n      members on all 3 nodes\n- [ ] No `ha-mode` policies remain on any vhost\n- [ ] `app-client` and `app-producer` publishing/consuming without errors\n- [ ] `ops-client` operational\n- [ ] Prometheus metrics endpoint reachable at `:15692/metrics`\n- [ ] `queue_master_locator` removed from running config\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":158,"cache_read_input_tokens":41543,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":158},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a73a9b8-ff7b-4701-9712-25cb1b94fa82","uuid":"91a1a937-f470-4adb-b394-8355e0290135","request_id":"req_011CcMUqCTLeKkKQgjYyW5Ky"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UAtiahP6MsTUNzMhpZkXuK","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /tmp/plan.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a73a9b8-ff7b-4701-9712-25cb1b94fa82","uuid":"66f47695-20ef-4040-9590-d0c77b2901ba","timestamp":"2026-06-24T04:49:57.849Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e5b25a86-cluster-a`\n**Author:** Operations Team (pre-change-window audit)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as found)\n\n### 1.1 Software Versions\n\n| Component | Version |\n|-----------|---------|\n| RabbitMQ  | **3.12.14** — out of support (EOL) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25 (erts-13.2.2.15) |\n\nAll three nodes are running identical versions.\n\n### 1.2 Cluster Topology\n\n- **Nodes:** 3 disk nodes (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2)\n- **Cluster name:** `rabbit@rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local`\n- **Peer discovery:** Kubernetes headless service (`rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s`)\n- **Partition handling:** `pause_minority`\n- **No alarms, no network partitions, no nodes under maintenance**\n\n### 1.3 Enabled Plugins\n\n`rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`,\n`rabbitmq_management_agent`\n\n### 1.4 Virtual Hosts\n\n| vhost  | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `/`    | Default (no application queues) |\n| `/app` | Application workload |\n| `/ops` | Operations/monitoring workload |\n\n### 1.5 Users and Permissions\n\n| User       | Tags          | `/`          | `/app`       | `/ops`       |\n|------------|---------------|--------------|--------------|--------------|\n| `admin`    | administrator | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |\n| `app-user` | management    | —            | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | —            |\n| `ops-user` | management    | —            | —            | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |\n\n### 1.6 Queues\n\n| vhost  | Queue       | Type    | Durable | Messages | Consumers |\n|--------|-------------|---------|---------|----------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | yes     | 575      | 0         |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | yes     | 0        | 0         |\n\n`app-queue` has **575 unprocessed messages and no active consumers** — a backlog risk.\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\n| vhost  | Name     | Pattern | Applies-to | Definition | Priority |\n|--------|----------|---------|------------|------------|----------|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `.*`    | queues     | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n\nNo policies on `/ops` or `/`.\n\n### 1.8 Exchanges and Bindings (/app)\n\nDefault AMQP exchanges only (amq.direct, amq.topic, amq.fanout, amq.headers, amq.match).\n`app-queue` is bound to the default exchange with routing key `app-queue`.\n\n### 1.9 Feature Flags (all enabled)\n\n`classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`,\n`stream_single_active_consumer`, `maintenance_mode_status`, `feature_flags_v2`,\n`user_limits`, `virtual_host_metadata`, and others — full set enabled.\n\n### 1.10 Key Config Settings\n\n```\ncluster_partition_handling = pause_minority\nqueue_master_locator       = min-masters\nloopback_users.guest       = false\nlisteners.tcp.default      = 5672\nmanagement.tcp.port        = 15672\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues Identified\n\n### P0 — Critical (must resolve before upgrade)\n\n**P0-1: Classic mirrored queues — deprecated and removed in 4.0**\nThe `ha-all` policy on `/app` uses `ha-mode: all` (classic mirroring). Classic\nmirrored queues were deprecated in 3.13 and **fully removed in 4.0**. Both\n`app-queue` (classic) and `ops-queue` (classic, no policy) must be converted to\nquorum queues before upgrading to 4.x.\n\n**P0-2: RabbitMQ 3.12.x is end-of-life**\n3.12 no longer receives security patches. Upgrade is required.\n\n**P0-3: 575 unread messages in `app-queue` with zero consumers**\nThe `app-client` consumer appears disconnected. These messages will be lost if the\nqueue is deleted during migration. Must drain or snapshot before any destructive\nqueue operation.\n\n### P1 — Should fix before next release\n\n**P1-1: `queue_master_locator = min-masters` is deprecated**\nThis setting is ignored by quorum/stream queues and has been removed in 4.x.\nRemove from `rabbitmq.conf` when updating config for the upgrade.\n\n**P1-2: `app-user` and `ops-user` have full permissions (`.*`)**\nPrinciple of least privilege: application users should be scoped to the queues and\nexchanges they actually use. Broadening to `.*` on configure allows these users to\ndeclare/delete any resource in their vhost.\n\n**P1-3: No HA/durability policy on `/ops` vhost**\n`ops-queue` is a classic durable queue but has no resilience policy. If it requires\nthe same availability guarantee as `app-queue`, it needs a quorum-queue policy.\n\n### P2 — Observe / low-priority\n\n**P2-1: Erlang/OTP 25 must be updated alongside RabbitMQ**\nRabbitMQ 4.x requires Erlang 26+. The Erlang upgrade must be bundled into the same\nimage change.\n\n**P2-2: No dead-letter exchange (DLX) on `app-queue`**\nWith 575 stale messages and no DLX, rejected or TTL-expired messages are silently\ndropped. Consider adding a DLX for operational visibility.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Required Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ does not support skipping major versions. The mandatory sequence:\n\n```\n3.12.14 (current, EOL)\n  -> 3.13.x   [Erlang 26+]   classic mirroring deprecated but still functional\n  -> 4.0.x    [Erlang 26+]   classic mirroring REMOVED; quorum queues required by here\n  -> 4.1.x    [Erlang 26+]   current stable\n```\n\nEach hop is a rolling StatefulSet upgrade: one pod at a time, verify the node\nrejoins the cluster before proceeding to the next pod.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Change Plan — Step-by-Step\n\n> **IMPORTANT: None of these steps have been applied. This plan requires sign-off\n> before execution. Apply only during the scheduled change window with a rollback\n> engineer available.**\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (day of change window, before any changes)\n\n1. Confirm cluster health:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n   ```\n   All 3 nodes must be Running. Zero alarms. No network partitions.\n\n2. Snapshot `app-queue` messages. If `app-client` can be restarted, do so and\n   wait for `messages = 0`. Otherwise export a definitions + message backup:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json\n   # Use rabbitmqadmin or the HTTP API to shovel/export messages if needed.\n   ```\n\n3. Export definitions backup (also covers vhosts, users, permissions, policies):\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json\n   ```\n\n4. Confirm `app-producer` and `app-client` pod health in Kubernetes.\n\n### Phase 1 — Migrate queues to Quorum (on 3.12.14, before any version bump)\n\nQuorum queues are already supported on 3.12 and all feature flags are enabled.\n\n**Step 1a — Remove the classic ha-all policy on /app:**\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all\n```\n\n**Step 1b — Add a quorum-queue policy on /app:**\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app quorum-default \".*\" \\\n  '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' \\\n  --apply-to queues --priority 0\n```\nThis policy governs newly declared queues. Existing classic queues must be\nre-declared.\n\n**Step 1c — Migrate app-queue (classic -> quorum):**\n- Pause producers: scale `app-producer` Deployment to 0.\n- Drain `app-queue` to 0 messages (consumers, or shovel to a staging queue).\n- Delete the classic queue:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n  ```\n- Re-declare as quorum:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqadmin -V /app declare queue name=app-queue durable=true \\\n    arguments='{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}'\n  ```\n- Resume producers: scale `app-producer` back to 1.\n\n**Step 1d — Migrate ops-queue (classic -> quorum):**\n- Apply a quorum policy on /ops:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /ops quorum-default \".*\" \\\n    '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' --apply-to queues --priority 0\n  ```\n- Delete and re-declare `ops-queue`:\n  ```bash\n  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /ops ops-queue\n  rabbitmqadmin -V /ops declare queue name=ops-queue durable=true \\\n    arguments='{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}'\n  ```\n\n**Step 1e — Verify quorum queues:**\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state leader members\nrabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state leader members\n```\nEach queue must show `type=quorum`, a `leader` on one node, and `members` listing\nall three nodes.\n\n### Phase 2 — Update rabbitmq.conf\n\nRemove `queue_master_locator = min-masters` from the ConfigMap or Secret backing\n`rabbitmq.conf`. Apply via a rolling restart of the StatefulSet after Phase 1 is\nverified stable.\n\n### Phase 3 — Version Upgrade: 3.12.14 -> 3.13.x\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image tag to the target 3.13.x image (with Erlang 26 base).\n2. Rolling upgrade — one pod at a time in reverse ordinal order (rabbitmq-2 first):\n   ```bash\n   # Use a partition-based rolling update or manual pod-by-pod:\n   kubectl rollout restart statefulset/rabbitmq -n <ns>\n   ```\n   After each pod restarts, wait until it rejoins:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl cluster_status | grep -A5 \"Running Nodes\"\n   ```\n3. After all pods are on 3.13.x, enable any new feature flags:\n   ```bash\n   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n   ```\n4. Verify: all alarms clear, quorum queues healthy, consumers reconnected.\n\n### Phase 4 — Version Upgrade: 3.13.x -> 4.0.x or 4.1.x\n\nRepeat the rolling upgrade procedure with the 4.0.x or 4.1.x image. At this point\nclassic mirrored queues must already be gone (Phase 1). Verify no `ha-mode` policies\nremain before starting:\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl list_policies --all-vhosts\n# Must show no ha-mode definitions\n```\n\nEnable remaining 4.x feature flags post-upgrade:\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n```\n\n### Phase 5 — Tighten Permissions (P1-2, post-upgrade)\n\nScope `app-user` and `ops-user` to least privilege after the upgrade is confirmed stable:\n\n```bash\n# app-user: write and read only to app-queue; no configure rights\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"\" \"^app-queue$\" \"^app-queue$\"\n\n# ops-user: write and read only to ops-queue; no configure rights\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \"\" \"^ops-queue$\" \"^ops-queue$\"\n```\n\nTest application connectivity before removing broader permissions.\n\n### Phase 6 — Add DLX to app-queue (P2-2, optional / future window)\n\nDeclare a dead-letter exchange on `/app` and attach it to `app-queue` via the\n`x-dead-letter-exchange` argument. This requires another queue re-declaration\n(safe since Phase 1 already converted it to quorum).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\n| Phase | Rollback Action |\n|-------|----------------|\n| Phase 1 (policy + queue type) | Re-apply `ha-all` policy; restore classic queues from definitions backup |\n| Phase 2 (config) | Restore previous `rabbitmq.conf` from ConfigMap backup; rolling restart |\n| Phase 3 (3.13 upgrade) | Roll back StatefulSet image to 3.12.14; rolling restart. Note: some 3.13 feature flags are not reversible |\n| Phase 4 (4.x upgrade) | Roll back to 3.13.x image. Classic queue removal in 4.x is irreversible — do not attempt to roll back to classic queues from 4.x |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Acceptance Criteria\n\nAfter the change window, verify ALL of the following before sign-off:\n\n- [ ] All 3 nodes running the target version (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`)\n- [ ] No alarms (`rabbitmqctl list_alarms`)\n- [ ] `app-queue` and `ops-queue` are type `quorum`, each with a leader and\n      members on all 3 nodes\n- [ ] No `ha-mode` policies remain on any vhost\n- [ ] `app-client` and `app-producer` publishing/consuming without errors\n- [ ] `ops-client` operational\n- [ ] Prometheus metrics endpoint reachable at `:15692/metrics`\n- [ ] `queue_master_locator` removed from running config\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":8,"newStart":1,"newLines":8,"lines":[" # RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan"," ","-**Prepared:** 2026-06-23  ","-**Cluster namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e44cf02f-cluster-a  ","-**Author:** Operations Team","+**Prepared:** 2026-06-23","+**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e5b25a86-cluster-a`","+**Author:** Operations Team (pre-change-window audit)"," "," ---"," "]},{"oldStart":12,"oldLines":326,"newStart":12,"newLines":304,"lines":[" "," | Component | Version |"," |-----------|---------|","-| RabbitMQ  | 3.12.14 |","-| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts-13.2.2.11) |","-| Container image | rabbitmq:3.12-management |","-| Support status | **Out of support** (3.12 series EOL) |","+| RabbitMQ  | **3.12.14** — out of support (EOL) |","+| Erlang/OTP | 25 (erts-13.2.2.15) |"," ","-All three nodes run identical versions — the cluster is homogeneous.","+All three nodes are running identical versions."," ","-### 1.2 Node Topology","+### 1.2 Cluster Topology"," ","-3-node all-disk cluster, all healthy, no maintenance mode, no alarms, no network partitions.","+- **Nodes:** 3 disk nodes (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2)","+- **Cluster name:** `rabbit@rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local`","+- **Peer discovery:** Kubernetes headless service (`rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s`)","+- **Partition handling:** `pause_minority`","+- **No alarms, no network partitions, no nodes under maintenance**"," ","-```","-rabbit@rabbitmq-0   running   10 CPU cores","-rabbit@rabbitmq-1   running   10 CPU cores","-rabbit@rabbitmq-2   running   10 CPU cores","-```","-"," ### 1.3 Enabled Plugins"," ","-- rabbitmq_management / rabbitmq_management_agent","-- rabbitmq_prometheus","-- rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s / rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common","+`rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management`,","+`rabbitmq_management_agent`"," "," ### 1.4 Virtual Hosts"," ","-| vhost | Purpose |","-|-------|---------|","-| `/`   | Default (admin-only access) |","-| `/app` | Application workloads |","-| `/ops` | Operations/tooling workloads |","+| vhost  | Purpose |","+|--------|---------|","+| `/`    | Default (no application queues) |","+| `/app` | Application workload |","+| `/ops` | Operations/monitoring workload |"," "," ### 1.5 Users and Permissions"," ","-| User | Tags | `/` | `/app` | `/ops` |","-|------|------|-----|--------|--------|","-| admin | administrator | .* / .* / .* | .* / .* / .* | .* / .* / .* |","-| app-user | management | — | .* / .* / .* | — |","-| ops-user | management | — | — | .* / .* / .* |","+| User       | Tags          | `/`          | `/app`       | `/ops`       |","+|------------|---------------|--------------|--------------|--------------|","+| `admin`    | administrator | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |","+| `app-user` | management    | —            | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` | —            |","+| `ops-user` | management    | —            | —            | `.*`/`.*`/`.*` |"," ","-Permissions notation: configure / write / read.","-"," ### 1.6 Queues"," ","-| vhost | Queue name | Type | Durable | State | Arguments |","-|-------|-----------|------|---------|-------|-----------|","-| /app | app-queue | classic | true | running | x-queue-type=classic |","-| /ops | ops-queue | classic | true | running | x-queue-type=classic |","+| vhost  | Queue       | Type    | Durable | Messages | Consumers |","+|--------|-------------|---------|---------|----------|-----------|","+| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | yes     | 575      | 0         |","+| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | yes     | 0        | 0         |"," ","-Both queues use the default exchange binding (routing key = queue name).","+`app-queue` has **575 unprocessed messages and no active consumers** — a backlog risk."," "," ### 1.7 Policies"," ","-| vhost | Policy name | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |","-|-------|------------|---------|----------|-----------|---------|","-| /app | ha-all | .* | queues | {\"ha-mode\":\"all\"} | 0 |","-| /ops | (none) | — | — | — | — |","-| / | (none) | — | — | — | — |","+| vhost  | Name     | Pattern | Applies-to | Definition | Priority |","+|--------|----------|---------|------------|------------|----------|","+| `/app` | `ha-all` | `.*`    | queues     | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |"," ","-### 1.8 Feature Flags (all enabled)","+No policies on `/ops` or `/`."," ","-All feature flags through the 3.12 series are enabled, including quorum_queue,","-stream_queue, classic_mirrored_queue_version, maintenance_mode_status,","-feature_flags_v2, and virtual_host_metadata.","+### 1.8 Exchanges and Bindings (/app)"," ","----","+Default AMQP exchanges only (amq.direct, amq.topic, amq.fanout, amq.headers, amq.match).","+`app-queue` is bound to the default exchange with routing key `app-queue`."," ","-## 2. Risk Assessment","+### 1.9 Feature Flags (all enabled)"," ","-### 2.1 Critical Issues Requiring Action Before Upgrade to 4.0","+`classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`,","+`stream_single_active_consumer`, `maintenance_mode_status`, `feature_flags_v2`,","+`user_limits`, `virtual_host_metadata`, and others — full set enabled."," ","-**Classic Mirrored Queues (CMQ) — HIGH RISK**","+### 1.10 Key Config Settings"," ","-The ha-all policy on vhost /app enables classic queue mirroring","-(\"ha-mode\":\"all\"). Classic mirrored queues were deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.12","-and are removed entirely in RabbitMQ 4.0. The app-queue is declared as a","-classic queue and is currently governed by this policy.","+```","+cluster_partition_handling = pause_minority","+queue_master_locator       = min-masters","+loopback_users.guest       = false","+listeners.tcp.default      = 5672","+management.tcp.port        = 15672","+```"," ","-Consequences if not addressed before upgrading to 4.0:","-- Cluster nodes may refuse to restart after upgrade if CMQ metadata is present.","-- The ha-all policy will be silently ignored and queues become non-replicated.","+---"," ","-Action required: migrate app-queue to a quorum queue and remove the ha-all","-policy before upgrading past 3.13.","+## 2. Issues Identified"," ","-### 2.2 Supported Upgrade Path","+### P0 — Critical (must resolve before upgrade)"," ","-RabbitMQ supports upgrading one minor version at a time:","+**P0-1: Classic mirrored queues — deprecated and removed in 4.0**","+The `ha-all` policy on `/app` uses `ha-mode: all` (classic mirroring). Classic","+mirrored queues were deprecated in 3.13 and **fully removed in 4.0**. Both","+`app-queue` (classic) and `ops-queue` (classic, no policy) must be converted to","+quorum queues before upgrading to 4.x."," ","-  3.12.14  →  3.13.x  →  4.0.x","+**P0-2: RabbitMQ 3.12.x is end-of-life**","+3.12 no longer receives security patches. Upgrade is required."," ","-Direct jump from 3.12 to 4.0 is not supported.","+**P0-3: 575 unread messages in `app-queue` with zero consumers**","+The `app-client` consumer appears disconnected. These messages will be lost if the","+queue is deleted during migration. Must drain or snapshot before any destructive","+queue operation."," ","-### 2.3 Erlang Version Requirement","+### P1 — Should fix before next release"," ","-RabbitMQ 3.13 requires Erlang 26; RabbitMQ 4.0 requires Erlang 26+.","-The current image (3.12-management) ships Erlang 25. The new image tags","-(3.13-management, 4.0-management) bundle the correct Erlang version automatically.","+**P1-1: `queue_master_locator = min-masters` is deprecated**","+This setting is ignored by quorum/stream queues and has been removed in 4.x.","+Remove from `rabbitmq.conf` when updating config for the upgrade."," ","----","+**P1-2: `app-user` and `ops-user` have full permissions (`.*`)**","+Principle of least privilege: application users should be scoped to the queues and","+exchanges they actually use. Broadening to `.*` on configure allows these users to","+declare/delete any resource in their vhost."," ","-## 3. Change Plan","+**P1-3: No HA/durability policy on `/ops` vhost**","+`ops-queue` is a classic durable queue but has no resilience policy. If it requires","+the same availability guarantee as `app-queue`, it needs a quorum-queue policy."," ","-### Phase 0 — Pre-change Checklist (day of change window)","+### P2 — Observe / low-priority"," ","-1. Verify all 3 nodes are running and not under maintenance:","-     rabbitmqctl cluster_status","+**P2-1: Erlang/OTP 25 must be updated alongside RabbitMQ**","+RabbitMQ 4.x requires Erlang 26+. The Erlang upgrade must be bundled into the same","+image change."," ","-2. Confirm no alarms:","-     rabbitmqctl status | grep -A5 Alarms","+**P2-2: No dead-letter exchange (DLX) on `app-queue`**","+With 575 stale messages and no DLX, rejected or TTL-expired messages are silently","+dropped. Consider adding a DLX for operational visibility."," ","-3. Record current message counts on all queues:","-     rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name messages messages_ready messages_unacknowledged","-     rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name messages messages_ready messages_unacknowledged","-","-4. Snapshot all definitions to a backup file:","-     rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-pre-migration.json","-   Copy the file out of the pod before proceeding.","-","-5. Take a PVC volume snapshot for each node's data volume (via VolumeSnapshot or","-   storage provider API) to enable rollback.","-"," ---"," ","-### Phase 1 — Migrate Classic Queues to Quorum Queues","+## 3. Required Upgrade Path"," ","-Goal: eliminate all CMQ usage before the 3.12 -> 3.13 upgrade.","+RabbitMQ does not support skipping major versions. The mandatory sequence:"," ","-#### 1a. Pause producers on /app","+```","+3.12.14 (current, EOL)","+  -> 3.13.x   [Erlang 26+]   classic mirroring deprecated but still functional","+  -> 4.0.x    [Erlang 26+]   classic mirroring REMOVED; quorum queues required by here","+  -> 4.1.x    [Erlang 26+]   current stable","+```"," ","-Coordinate with application teams to temporarily stop or redirect producers","-writing to app-queue. Drain in-flight messages to zero before migrating.","+Each hop is a rolling StatefulSet upgrade: one pod at a time, verify the node","+rejoins the cluster before proceeding to the next pod."," ","-#### 1b. Create replacement quorum queue","-","-  curl -u admin:<password> -X PUT \\","-    http://rabbitmq-0:15672/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue-quorum \\","-    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\","-    -d '{\"durable\":true,\"arguments\":{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}}'","-","-#### 1c. Migrate bindings","-","-The current app-queue uses only the default exchange binding (auto-created by","-queue name). The replacement queue gets the same binding automatically. If named","-exchanges or routing keys are in use, re-bind accordingly.","-","-#### 1d. Drain app-queue into app-queue-quorum using Shovel","-","-  rabbitmqctl -p /app set_parameter shovel drain-shovel \\","-    '{\"src-protocol\":\"amqp091\",\"src-uri\":\"amqp://\",\"src-queue\":\"app-queue\",","-      \"dest-protocol\":\"amqp091\",\"dest-uri\":\"amqp://\",\"dest-queue\":\"app-queue-quorum\",","-      \"delete-after\":\"queue-length\"}'","-","-Monitor until app-queue reaches 0 messages, then clear the shovel:","-","-  rabbitmqctl -p /app clear_parameter shovel drain-shovel","-","-#### 1e. Remove the CMQ policy","-","-  rabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all","-","-#### 1f. Delete the old classic queue","-","-  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue","-","-#### 1g. Rename app-queue-quorum -> app-queue (if application requires original name)","-","-RabbitMQ does not support in-place rename. To restore the original name:","-  1. Confirm app-queue-quorum is empty and has no consumers.","-  2. Delete it and recreate as a quorum queue named app-queue:","-","-     curl -u admin:<password> -X PUT \\","-       http://rabbitmq-0:15672/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue \\","-       -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\","-       -d '{\"durable\":true,\"arguments\":{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}}'","-","-  Alternatively, update application configuration to use the new queue name.","-","-#### 1h. Add a quorum-queue policy for /app (recommended)","-","-Replace the removed CMQ policy with a quorum-oriented policy:","-","-  rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app ha-quorum \".*\" \\","-    '{\"x-quorum-initial-group-size\":3}' --apply-to queues --priority 0","-","-This ensures all new queues in /app are created with 3 replicas (one per node).","-","-#### 1i. Consider migrating ops-queue in /ops (recommended)","-","-ops-queue is currently a classic queue with no HA policy. Although it is not","-subject to a CMQ policy today, migrating it to a quorum queue during this window","-provides resilience and consistency. Apply the same drain-and-recreate procedure.","-"," ---"," ","-### Phase 2 — Upgrade RabbitMQ 3.12 -> 3.13","+## 4. Change Plan — Step-by-Step"," ","-Goal: move to a supported release series.","+> **IMPORTANT: None of these steps have been applied. This plan requires sign-off","+> before execution. Apply only during the scheduled change window with a rollback","+> engineer available.**"," ","-#### 2a. Target image","+### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (day of change window, before any changes)"," ","-  rabbitmq:3.13-management","+1. Confirm cluster health:","+   ```bash","+   rabbitmqctl cluster_status","+   ```","+   All 3 nodes must be Running. Zero alarms. No network partitions."," ","-Pin to a specific patch version (e.g., rabbitmq:3.13.7-management). Verify the","-latest stable patch at https://hub.docker.com/_/rabbitmq before the change window.","+2. Snapshot `app-queue` messages. If `app-client` can be restarted, do so and","+   wait for `messages = 0`. Otherwise export a definitions + message backup:","+   ```bash","+   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json","+   # Use rabbitmqadmin or the HTTP API to shovel/export messages if needed.","+   ```"," ","-#### 2b. Rolling upgrade via StatefulSet","+3. Export definitions backup (also covers vhosts, users, permissions, policies):","+   ```bash","+   rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-backup.json","+   ```"," ","-RabbitMQ supports rolling upgrades one minor version at a time. Update the","-StatefulSet image to allow Kubernetes to roll pods one at a time (maxUnavailable: 1).","+4. Confirm `app-producer` and `app-client` pod health in Kubernetes."," ","-  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e44cf02f-cluster-a \\","-    set image statefulset/rabbitmq rabbitmq=rabbitmq:3.13.7-management","+### Phase 1 — Migrate queues to Quorum (on 3.12.14, before any version bump)"," ","-Monitor rollout:","+Quorum queues are already supported on 3.12 and all feature flags are enabled."," ","-  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e44cf02f-cluster-a \\","-    rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq","+**Step 1a — Remove the classic ha-all policy on /app:**","+```bash","+rabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all","+```"," ","-After each pod restarts, verify it rejoined the cluster:","+**Step 1b — Add a quorum-queue policy on /app:**","+```bash","+rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app quorum-default \".*\" \\","+  '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' \\","+  --apply-to queues --priority 0","+```","+This policy governs newly declared queues. Existing classic queues must be","+re-declared."," ","-  rabbitmqctl cluster_status","+**Step 1c — Migrate app-queue (classic -> quorum):**","+- Pause producers: scale `app-producer` Deployment to 0.","+- Drain `app-queue` to 0 messages (consumers, or shovel to a staging queue).","+- Delete the classic queue:","+  ```bash","+  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue","+  ```","+- Re-declare as quorum:","+  ```bash","+  rabbitmqadmin -V /app declare queue name=app-queue durable=true \\","+    arguments='{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}'","+  ```","+- Resume producers: scale `app-producer` back to 1."," ","-#### 2c. Enable 3.13 feature flags","+**Step 1d — Migrate ops-queue (classic -> quorum):**","+- Apply a quorum policy on /ops:","+  ```bash","+  rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /ops quorum-default \".*\" \\","+    '{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}' --apply-to queues --priority 0","+  ```","+- Delete and re-declare `ops-queue`:","+  ```bash","+  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /ops ops-queue","+  rabbitmqadmin -V /ops declare queue name=ops-queue durable=true \\","+    arguments='{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}'","+  ```"," ","-After all nodes are on 3.13:","+**Step 1e — Verify quorum queues:**","+```bash","+rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state leader members","+rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type state leader members","+```","+Each queue must show `type=quorum`, a `leader` on one node, and `members` listing","+all three nodes."," ","-  rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all","+### Phase 2 — Update rabbitmq.conf"," ","-Verify all flags show enabled:","+Remove `queue_master_locator = min-masters` from the ConfigMap or Secret backing","+`rabbitmq.conf`. Apply via a rolling restart of the StatefulSet after Phase 1 is","+verified stable."," ","-  rabbitmqctl list_feature_flags","+### Phase 3 — Version Upgrade: 3.12.14 -> 3.13.x"," ","-#### 2d. Post-upgrade smoke test","+1. Update the StatefulSet image tag to the target 3.13.x image (with Erlang 26 base).","+2. Rolling upgrade — one pod at a time in reverse ordinal order (rabbitmq-2 first):","+   ```bash","+   # Use a partition-based rolling update or manual pod-by-pod:","+   kubectl rollout restart statefulset/rabbitmq -n <ns>","+   ```","+   After each pod restarts, wait until it rejoins:","+   ```bash","+   rabbitmqctl cluster_status | grep -A5 \"Running Nodes\"","+   ```","+3. After all pods are on 3.13.x, enable any new feature flags:","+   ```bash","+   rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all","+   ```","+4. Verify: all alarms clear, quorum queues healthy, consumers reconnected."," ","-  rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type messages","-  rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type messages","-  rabbitmqctl list_policies -p /app","-  rabbitmqctl cluster_status","+### Phase 4 — Version Upgrade: 3.13.x -> 4.0.x or 4.1.x"," ","----","+Repeat the rolling upgrade procedure with the 4.0.x or 4.1.x image. At this point","+classic mirrored queues must already be gone (Phase 1). Verify no `ha-mode` policies","+remain before starting:","+```bash","+rabbitmqctl list_policies --all-vhosts","+# Must show no ha-mode definitions","+```"," ","-### Phase 3 — Upgrade RabbitMQ 3.13 -> 4.0 (separate change window)","+Enable remaining 4.x feature flags post-upgrade:","+```bash","+rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all","+```"," ","-Schedule as a separate change window after Phase 2 has been stable for at","-least one week.","+### Phase 5 — Tighten Permissions (P1-2, post-upgrade)"," ","-#### 3a. Prerequisites","+Scope `app-user` and `ops-user` to least privilege after the upgrade is confirmed stable:"," ","-- All feature flags from Phase 2c must be enabled.","-- No classic mirrored queue policies or CMQ metadata may exist (completed in Phase 1).","-- Re-export definitions backup from 3.13 node before proceeding.","+```bash","+# app-user: write and read only to app-queue; no configure rights","+rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"\" \"^app-queue$\" \"^app-queue$\""," ","-#### 3b. Target image","+# ops-user: write and read only to ops-queue; no configure rights","+rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \"\" \"^ops-queue$\" \"^ops-queue$\"","+```"," ","-  rabbitmq:4.0-management (pin to specific patch, e.g., rabbitmq:4.0.9-management)","+Test application connectivity before removing broader permissions."," ","-#### 3c. Rolling upgrade","+### Phase 6 — Add DLX to app-queue (P2-2, optional / future window)"," ","-Same procedure as Phase 2b, updating image to rabbitmq:4.0.x-management.","+Declare a dead-letter exchange on `/app` and attach it to `app-queue` via the","+`x-dead-letter-exchange` argument. This requires another queue re-declaration","+(safe since Phase 1 already converted it to quorum)."," ","-#### 3d. Enable 4.0 feature flags","-","-  rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all","-","-#### 3e. Breaking changes to review before 4.0","-","-- Classic mirrored queues are fully removed — must be completed in Phase 1.","-- Management HTTP API v1 endpoints have stricter validation in 4.0.","-- Default consumer_timeout changed; audit application consumer acknowledgement","-  patterns to ensure they are within the new timeout.","-- Stream queue and quorum queue configuration defaults changed; review any","-  explicit x- arguments set on stream queues.","-"," ---"," ","-## 4. Rollback Plan","+## 5. Rollback Plan"," ","-### Phase 1 rollback (queue type migration)","+| Phase | Rollback Action |","+|-------|----------------|","+| Phase 1 (policy + queue type) | Re-apply `ha-all` policy; restore classic queues from definitions backup |","+| Phase 2 (config) | Restore previous `rabbitmq.conf` from ConfigMap backup; rolling restart |","+| Phase 3 (3.13 upgrade) | Roll back StatefulSet image to 3.12.14; rolling restart. Note: some 3.13 feature flags are not reversible |","+| Phase 4 (4.x upgrade) | Roll back to 3.13.x image. Classic queue removal in 4.x is irreversible — do not attempt to roll back to classic queues from 4.x |"," ","-If the quorum queue migration causes problems before the old classic queue is","-deleted, revert by:","-  1. Clearing the Shovel if active.","-  2. Redirecting producers back to the original app-queue.","-  3. Re-applying the ha-all CMQ policy:","-       rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app ha-all \".*\" '{\"ha-mode\":\"all\"}' \\","-         --apply-to queues --priority 0","-","-Once app-queue is deleted, rollback requires restoring from the definitions","-backup and from the PVC snapshot taken in Phase 0.","-","-### Phase 2 rollback (3.13 upgrade)","-","-Downgrading RabbitMQ is not supported once feature flags introduced in the","-higher version are enabled. The only safe rollback is:","-  1. Restore PVC data from the pre-upgrade snapshot.","-  2. Restore definitions from the Phase 0 export.","-  3. Roll the StatefulSet image back to rabbitmq:3.12-management.","-","-This is a destructive rollback — any messages published after the snapshot are lost.","-","-### Phase 3 rollback (4.0 upgrade)","-","-Same procedure as Phase 2 rollback, using the 3.13 PVC snapshot and restoring","-the image to rabbitmq:3.13.x-management.","-"," ---"," ","-## 5. Summary of Planned Changes","+## 6. Acceptance Criteria"," ","-| # | Change | Scope | Risk Level |","-|---|--------|-------|-----------|","-| 1 | Remove ha-all CMQ policy | /app vhost | Medium |","-| 2 | Migrate app-queue: classic -> quorum | /app vhost | Medium |","-| 3 | Add ha-quorum quorum queue policy | /app vhost | Low |","-| 4 | Migrate ops-queue: classic -> quorum (optional) | /ops vhost | Low |","-| 5 | Rolling upgrade: 3.12 -> 3.13 | Cluster (all nodes) | Medium |","-| 6 | Enable 3.13 feature flags | Cluster | Low (irreversible) |","-| 7 | Rolling upgrade: 3.13 -> 4.0 (next window) | Cluster (all nodes) | Medium |","-| 8 | Enable 4.0 feature flags | Cluster | Low (irreversible) |","+After the change window, verify ALL of the following before sign-off:"," ","-**No changes are applied by this document.** All steps in Section 3 are to be","-executed during the approved change window after this plan is reviewed and","-signed off by the operations team.","+- [ ] All 3 nodes running the target version (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`)","+- [ ] No alarms (`rabbitmqctl list_alarms`)","+- [ ] `app-queue` and `ops-queue` are type `quorum`, each with a leader and","+      members on all 3 nodes","+- [ ] No `ha-mode` policies remain on any vhost","+- [ ] `app-client` and `app-producer` publishing/consuming without errors","+- [ ] `ops-client` operational","+- [ ] Prometheus metrics endpoint reachable at `:15692/metrics`","+- [ ] `queue_master_locator` removed from running config"]}],"originalFile":"# RabbitMQ Cluster Change / Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23  \n**Cluster namespace:** karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e44cf02f-cluster-a  \n**Author:** Operations Team\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as found)\n\n### 1.1 Software Versions\n\n| Component | Version |\n|-----------|---------|\n| RabbitMQ  | 3.12.14 |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts-13.2.2.11) |\n| Container image | rabbitmq:3.12-management |\n| Support status | **Out of support** (3.12 series EOL) |\n\nAll three nodes run identical versions — the cluster is homogeneous.\n\n### 1.2 Node Topology\n\n3-node all-disk cluster, all healthy, no maintenance mode, no alarms, no network partitions.\n\n```\nrabbit@rabbitmq-0   running   10 CPU cores\nrabbit@rabbitmq-1   running   10 CPU cores\nrabbit@rabbitmq-2   running   10 CPU cores\n```\n\n### 1.3 Enabled Plugins\n\n- rabbitmq_management / rabbitmq_management_agent\n- rabbitmq_prometheus\n- rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s / rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common\n\n### 1.4 Virtual Hosts\n\n| vhost | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `/`   | Default (admin-only access) |\n| `/app` | Application workloads |\n| `/ops` | Operations/tooling workloads |\n\n### 1.5 Users and Permissions\n\n| User | Tags | `/` | `/app` | `/ops` |\n|------|------|-----|--------|--------|\n| admin | administrator | .* / .* / .* | .* / .* / .* | .* / .* / .* |\n| app-user | management | — | .* / .* / .* | — |\n| ops-user | management | — | — | .* / .* / .* |\n\nPermissions notation: configure / write / read.\n\n### 1.6 Queues\n\n| vhost | Queue name | Type | Durable | State | Arguments |\n|-------|-----------|------|---------|-------|-----------|\n| /app | app-queue | classic | true | running | x-queue-type=classic |\n| /ops | ops-queue | classic | true | running | x-queue-type=classic |\n\nBoth queues use the default exchange binding (routing key = queue name).\n\n### 1.7 Policies\n\n| vhost | Policy name | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |\n|-------|------------|---------|----------|-----------|---------|\n| /app | ha-all | .* | queues | {\"ha-mode\":\"all\"} | 0 |\n| /ops | (none) | — | — | — | — |\n| / | (none) | — | — | — | — |\n\n### 1.8 Feature Flags (all enabled)\n\nAll feature flags through the 3.12 series are enabled, including quorum_queue,\nstream_queue, classic_mirrored_queue_version, maintenance_mode_status,\nfeature_flags_v2, and virtual_host_metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Risk Assessment\n\n### 2.1 Critical Issues Requiring Action Before Upgrade to 4.0\n\n**Classic Mirrored Queues (CMQ) — HIGH RISK**\n\nThe ha-all policy on vhost /app enables classic queue mirroring\n(\"ha-mode\":\"all\"). Classic mirrored queues were deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.12\nand are removed entirely in RabbitMQ 4.0. The app-queue is declared as a\nclassic queue and is currently governed by this policy.\n\nConsequences if not addressed before upgrading to 4.0:\n- Cluster nodes may refuse to restart after upgrade if CMQ metadata is present.\n- The ha-all policy will be silently ignored and queues become non-replicated.\n\nAction required: migrate app-queue to a quorum queue and remove the ha-all\npolicy before upgrading past 3.13.\n\n### 2.2 Supported Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ supports upgrading one minor version at a time:\n\n  3.12.14  →  3.13.x  →  4.0.x\n\nDirect jump from 3.12 to 4.0 is not supported.\n\n### 2.3 Erlang Version Requirement\n\nRabbitMQ 3.13 requires Erlang 26; RabbitMQ 4.0 requires Erlang 26+.\nThe current image (3.12-management) ships Erlang 25. The new image tags\n(3.13-management, 4.0-management) bundle the correct Erlang version automatically.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Change Plan\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-change Checklist (day of change window)\n\n1. Verify all 3 nodes are running and not under maintenance:\n     rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n\n2. Confirm no alarms:\n     rabbitmqctl status | grep -A5 Alarms\n\n3. Record current message counts on all queues:\n     rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name messages messages_ready messages_unacknowledged\n     rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name messages messages_ready messages_unacknowledged\n\n4. Snapshot all definitions to a backup file:\n     rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-pre-migration.json\n   Copy the file out of the pod before proceeding.\n\n5. Take a PVC volume snapshot for each node's data volume (via VolumeSnapshot or\n   storage provider API) to enable rollback.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 1 — Migrate Classic Queues to Quorum Queues\n\nGoal: eliminate all CMQ usage before the 3.12 -> 3.13 upgrade.\n\n#### 1a. Pause producers on /app\n\nCoordinate with application teams to temporarily stop or redirect producers\nwriting to app-queue. Drain in-flight messages to zero before migrating.\n\n#### 1b. Create replacement quorum queue\n\n  curl -u admin:<password> -X PUT \\\n    http://rabbitmq-0:15672/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue-quorum \\\n    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n    -d '{\"durable\":true,\"arguments\":{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}}'\n\n#### 1c. Migrate bindings\n\nThe current app-queue uses only the default exchange binding (auto-created by\nqueue name). The replacement queue gets the same binding automatically. If named\nexchanges or routing keys are in use, re-bind accordingly.\n\n#### 1d. Drain app-queue into app-queue-quorum using Shovel\n\n  rabbitmqctl -p /app set_parameter shovel drain-shovel \\\n    '{\"src-protocol\":\"amqp091\",\"src-uri\":\"amqp://\",\"src-queue\":\"app-queue\",\n      \"dest-protocol\":\"amqp091\",\"dest-uri\":\"amqp://\",\"dest-queue\":\"app-queue-quorum\",\n      \"delete-after\":\"queue-length\"}'\n\nMonitor until app-queue reaches 0 messages, then clear the shovel:\n\n  rabbitmqctl -p /app clear_parameter shovel drain-shovel\n\n#### 1e. Remove the CMQ policy\n\n  rabbitmqctl clear_policy -p /app ha-all\n\n#### 1f. Delete the old classic queue\n\n  rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue\n\n#### 1g. Rename app-queue-quorum -> app-queue (if application requires original name)\n\nRabbitMQ does not support in-place rename. To restore the original name:\n  1. Confirm app-queue-quorum is empty and has no consumers.\n  2. Delete it and recreate as a quorum queue named app-queue:\n\n     curl -u admin:<password> -X PUT \\\n       http://rabbitmq-0:15672/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue \\\n       -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n       -d '{\"durable\":true,\"arguments\":{\"x-queue-type\":\"quorum\"}}'\n\n  Alternatively, update application configuration to use the new queue name.\n\n#### 1h. Add a quorum-queue policy for /app (recommended)\n\nReplace the removed CMQ policy with a quorum-oriented policy:\n\n  rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app ha-quorum \".*\" \\\n    '{\"x-quorum-initial-group-size\":3}' --apply-to queues --priority 0\n\nThis ensures all new queues in /app are created with 3 replicas (one per node).\n\n#### 1i. Consider migrating ops-queue in /ops (recommended)\n\nops-queue is currently a classic queue with no HA policy. Although it is not\nsubject to a CMQ policy today, migrating it to a quorum queue during this window\nprovides resilience and consistency. Apply the same drain-and-recreate procedure.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2 — Upgrade RabbitMQ 3.12 -> 3.13\n\nGoal: move to a supported release series.\n\n#### 2a. Target image\n\n  rabbitmq:3.13-management\n\nPin to a specific patch version (e.g., rabbitmq:3.13.7-management). Verify the\nlatest stable patch at https://hub.docker.com/_/rabbitmq before the change window.\n\n#### 2b. Rolling upgrade via StatefulSet\n\nRabbitMQ supports rolling upgrades one minor version at a time. Update the\nStatefulSet image to allow Kubernetes to roll pods one at a time (maxUnavailable: 1).\n\n  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e44cf02f-cluster-a \\\n    set image statefulset/rabbitmq rabbitmq=rabbitmq:3.13.7-management\n\nMonitor rollout:\n\n  kubectl -n karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-e44cf02f-cluster-a \\\n    rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq\n\nAfter each pod restarts, verify it rejoined the cluster:\n\n  rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n\n#### 2c. Enable 3.13 feature flags\n\nAfter all nodes are on 3.13:\n\n  rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n\nVerify all flags show enabled:\n\n  rabbitmqctl list_feature_flags\n\n#### 2d. Post-upgrade smoke test\n\n  rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type messages\n  rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /ops name type messages\n  rabbitmqctl list_policies -p /app\n  rabbitmqctl cluster_status\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3 — Upgrade RabbitMQ 3.13 -> 4.0 (separate change window)\n\nSchedule as a separate change window after Phase 2 has been stable for at\nleast one week.\n\n#### 3a. Prerequisites\n\n- All feature flags from Phase 2c must be enabled.\n- No classic mirrored queue policies or CMQ metadata may exist (completed in Phase 1).\n- Re-export definitions backup from 3.13 node before proceeding.\n\n#### 3b. Target image\n\n  rabbitmq:4.0-management (pin to specific patch, e.g., rabbitmq:4.0.9-management)\n\n#### 3c. Rolling upgrade\n\nSame procedure as Phase 2b, updating image to rabbitmq:4.0.x-management.\n\n#### 3d. Enable 4.0 feature flags\n\n  rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all\n\n#### 3e. Breaking changes to review before 4.0\n\n- Classic mirrored queues are fully removed — must be completed in Phase 1.\n- Management HTTP API v1 endpoints have stricter validation in 4.0.\n- Default consumer_timeout changed; audit application consumer acknowledgement\n  patterns to ensure they are within the new timeout.\n- Stream queue and quorum queue configuration defaults changed; review any\n  explicit x- arguments set on stream queues.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Plan\n\n### Phase 1 rollback (queue type migration)\n\nIf the quorum queue migration causes problems before the old classic queue is\ndeleted, revert by:\n  1. Clearing the Shovel if active.\n  2. Redirecting producers back to the original app-queue.\n  3. Re-applying the ha-all CMQ policy:\n       rabbitmqctl set_policy -p /app ha-all \".*\" '{\"ha-mode\":\"all\"}' \\\n         --apply-to queues --priority 0\n\nOnce app-queue is deleted, rollback requires restoring from the definitions\nbackup and from the PVC snapshot taken in Phase 0.\n\n### Phase 2 rollback (3.13 upgrade)\n\nDowngrading RabbitMQ is not supported once feature flags introduced in the\nhigher version are enabled. The only safe rollback is:\n  1. Restore PVC data from the pre-upgrade snapshot.\n  2. Restore definitions from the Phase 0 export.\n  3. Roll the StatefulSet image back to rabbitmq:3.12-management.\n\nThis is a destructive rollback — any messages published after the snapshot are lost.\n\n### Phase 3 rollback (4.0 upgrade)\n\nSame procedure as Phase 2 rollback, using the 3.13 PVC snapshot and restoring\nthe image to rabbitmq:3.13.x-management.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Summary of Planned Changes\n\n| # | Change | Scope | Risk Level |\n|---|--------|-------|-----------|\n| 1 | Remove ha-all CMQ policy | /app vhost | Medium |\n| 2 | Migrate app-queue: classic -> quorum | /app vhost | Medium |\n| 3 | Add ha-quorum quorum queue policy | /app vhost | Low |\n| 4 | Migrate ops-queue: classic -> quorum (optional) | /ops vhost | Low |\n| 5 | Rolling upgrade: 3.12 -> 3.13 | Cluster (all nodes) | Medium |\n| 6 | Enable 3.13 feature flags | Cluster | Low (irreversible) |\n| 7 | Rolling upgrade: 3.13 -> 4.0 (next window) | Cluster (all nodes) | Medium |\n| 8 | Enable 4.0 feature flags | Cluster | Low (irreversible) |\n\n**No changes are applied by this document.** All steps in Section 3 are to be\nexecuted during the approved change window after this plan is reviewed and\nsigned off by the operations team.\n","userModified":false}}
